As we are dealing with the D6-brane of type IIA string theory, we can associate it to a 6-form in ten dimensions. However, when this form is lift to eleven dimensions, we find that it is only non-trivial in the presence of an isometric direction, i.e. in the presence of a KK-monopole of the eleven dimensional theory. 

The metric for the KK-monopole can be written as

